(ii) Within 6 months of the date of approval of the 1995 closures and realignments unless the community requests a postponement
as provided in paragraph (a)(7) of this section.

(5) These timeframes afford Federal Agencies sufficient time to assess their needs, submit initial expressions
of interest to the Department of Defense, and apply for the property. During this period, Agencies sponsoring public
benefit conveyances should also consider the suitability for such purposes. The Military Departments should provide
other Federal Agencies as full and complete information as practicable on the property in the Notice of Availability.
Requests for transfers of property submitted by other Federal Agencies will normally be accommodated. Decisions
on the transfer of property to other Federal Agencies shall be made by the Military Department concerned in consultation
