and fill to 40 percent, a canister preconditioning step detailed below, and then the exhaust emissions test. At this
point the refueling test departs from the evaporative test sequence. Instead, additional driving is conducted to
provide more opportunity for canister purge. This driving consists of a UDDS cycle followed by two New York City Cycles
(NYCC) and then by another UDDS. This driving schedule corresponds to the driving specified for the evaporative running
loss test, though not at the same high temperatures. After the driving, the above-described refueling procedure
is conducted. 




