A hearing participant from the Occupational Health Foundation testified (Tr. 213: 4/3): 



Based on our experience visiting plants and working with workers, we believe there's a critical need for language
to really spell out the program requirements for effective use of gloves. 
 



That participant also remarked (Tr. 215: 4/3): 
 



In 1988, occupational skin disease accounted for about one-fourth of all reported occupational illnesses. Even
